      "content": "but the thing is, it's not just \"science fiction\" to me. i've literally felt it. it feels like they're using the songs i already like to slip these things in so i don't notice. if someone wanted to do this, they wouldn't use a \"signal,\" they'd use something that sounds like part of the music. what kind of software or tools would someone actually use to hide these sub-audible frequencies in a standard audio file? like, how would they even mask it so well?",
